label: 21/11/1963 · Irving, TX
title: Park-It Market Service Call (Verified)
description: Ralph Yates performed a verified refrigeration service call at Park-It Market Drive-In Grocery, 2320 Shady Grove Road, Irving TX. He was dispatched around 10:30 AM, called in after 11:30 AM, and returned to TBSC around 12:30-1:00 PM. The compressor was out of oil. Documented by Shop Bill No. 8760, Invoice No. 36919 ($12.00 for 2-hour call).

title: First Yates Report
description: Ralph Leon Yates voluntarily contacts the Dallas FBI office to report picking up a hitchhiker he believes was Lee Harvey Oswald carrying a package of 'curtain rods'.

title: Formal FBI Interview
description: Yates appears at the FBI office with his uncle, J.O. Smith. He details the hitchhiker's questions about shooting the President from a window. Agents Arthur Carter and C. Ray Hall conduct the interview.

label: Nov 27, 1963 · Dallas, TX
title: Dempsey Jones FBI Interview
description: FBI Special Agent Arthur E. Carter interviewed Dempsey Jones at Route 4, Box 376, Dallas TX. Jones confirmed Yates told him about the hitchhiker before the assassination. He described Yates as 'a big talker who always talks about a lot of foolishness.' Jones said Yates mentioned the man had a package and discussed shooting the President from a building.

label: Nov 27, 1963 · Dallas, TX
title: J.R. Gilpin FBI Interview
description: FBI interviewed J.R. Gilpin, partner at Texas Butchers Supply Company. Gilpin located Shop Bill No. 8760 and Invoice No. 36919 documenting Yates' service call to Park-It Market in Irving on November 21, 1963. He confirmed dispatching Yates around 10:30 AM and calling him at the market around noon.

title: Signed Statement & Photo ID
description: Yates provides a sworn affidavit to SA C. Ray Hall. He positively identifies a photo of Oswald. He adds details about the hitchhiker showing him a picture of a man with a rifle.

title: Alibi Verification Check
description: FBI Agents re-interview Yates regarding discrepancies in his service call timeline. They confront him with the lack of a check stub from Charlie's Meat Market.

label: Jan 3, 1964 · Dallas, TX
title: Thomas Ayres FBI Interview
description: FBI Special Agent John T. Kesler interviewed Thomas Ayres at Charlie's Ranch Meat Market, 249 Wynnewood Village. Ayres was on duty November 20-21, 1963 but could not recall giving a check to a TBSC employee. He reviewed check stubs with negative results. Stated only one check is issued to TBSC each month.

label: Jan 3, 1964 · Dallas, TX
title: Donald Mask FBI Interview
description: FBI Special Agent John T. Kesler interviewed Donald Mask at Charlie's Ranch Meat Market. Mask was on duty November 21, 1963 but could not recall giving a check to a TBSC employee. Like Ayres, he confirmed only one check is typically issued to TBSC each month.

title: Polygraph Examination
description: Yates submits to a polygraph test administered by the FBI. The results are recorded as 'inconclusive' with no significant deception indicated.

title: Distressed Phone Call
description: Yates calls SA C. Ray Hall late at night, crying and emotionally upset. He returns the next morning (Jan 9) to discuss his family's history of mental illness.

title: Final Appearance & Hospitalization
description: Yates appears with his wife, carrying pills he claims his doctors are using to kill him. Following this visit, he is admitted to Woodlawn Hospital for psychiatric observation.
